Package org.ejvm.execution

Contains classes used to execute compiled eJVM bytecode.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    EjvmExecutionListener
    Provides an interface for listeners informed about the steps of the execution of an EjvmProgram.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    EjvmMachine
    Represents a machine capable of executing eJVM bytecode and acts as the machine's operating system.
    EjvmProcess
    Represents a process in an EjvmMachine to execute an EjvmProgram and manages the associated resources.
    EjvmProcessor
    Represents a processor capable of executing eJVM bytecode instructions.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    EjvmExecutionException.Reason
    This enum contains all reasons why an EjvmExecutionException may have been thrown.
    EjvmInstruction
    Contains all instructions executable by the EjvmProcessor.
    EjvmInstruction.ArgumentType
    Describes the types arguments to an eJVM instruction may have.
    EjvmProcess.OutputFormatter
    Simple enum to represent the output mode set for a process.
    EjvmProcess.ProcessState
    Simple enum to represent the process state.
    EjvmProcessor.ProcessorState
    Represents the state of the processor.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    EjvmExecutionException
    Exception thrown when an EjvmProcess causes an exception during execution.
    NotExecutableException
    Exception thrown when an EjvmProgram cannot be executed by the EjvmMachine.
